1. Added `event.preventDefault()` to prevent any default form submission behavior
2. Replaced blocking `alert()` calls with non-blocking notifications
3. Added proper error handling with visual feedback
4. Used async/await properly to handle the API call
5. Added CSS animations for smooth notification display

These changes will:
- Prevent page refreshes when saving evaluations
- Provide better user feedback without blocking the UI
- Handle errors more gracefully
- Keep the UI responsive during save operations

The database operations themselves don't cause page refreshes - it was likely the default form submission behavior or the blocking alerts that were causing the issue.

